div.p:
                6. A meer Penal law when 'tis broke; the forfeiture
is sufficient for the satisfaction of the offence, or trespasse;
but not in a mixt Law.

1. From the testimony of Iohn;

the first, yet the least, yet very strong
and full, vers. 32, 33.

There is great need of trial of this, for a man may read,
hear and understand externally, what ever another may;
and yet the whole Scripture a sealed Book.
